## Troubleshooting

### "No PDFs found"
- Verify directory path in `pdf-ingestion-pipeline.ts`
- Check Windows file path format: Use backslashes or forward slashes consistently
- Ensure PDFs are actually .pdf files (not .PDF)

### "CrossRef API errors"
- Add `CROSSREF_EMAIL` to .env (required by CrossRef)
- Check internet connection
- CrossRef has rate limits; slow processing is normal

### "Supabase connection failed"
- Verify `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY` in .env
- Check database is running
- Ensure schema has been applied (run SQL migrations first)

### "OCR quality issues"
- Some scanned PDFs may have poor text extraction
- Consider: `npm run ingest:pdfs --ocr-enabled` (requires Tesseract.js)
- Manually review papers with <500 character text extraction

