## 3. Quick Start Instructions

```markdown name=QUICK_START.md
# 🚀 Quick Start: PDF Ingestion Pipeline

## Step 1: Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

This installs:
- `pdf-parse` - PDF text extraction
- `@supabase/supabase-js` - Database client
- `node-fetch` - HTTP requests for CrossRef API
- `ts-node` - TypeScript execution
- `typescript` - TypeScript compiler

## Step 2: Configure Environment

Create `.env` file in project root:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env` with your Supabase credentials:

```
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
CROSSREF_EMAIL=your-email@coralfil.org
```

**Where to get credentials:**
- `SUPABASE_URL`: Go to https://app.supabase.com → Project Settings → API
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY`: Same page, copy "Service role" key (keep secret!)
- `CROSSREF_EMAIL`: Your email address (required by CrossRef API)

## Step 3: Verify PDF Directory

Ensure your PDFs are at:
```
C:\Users\User\Documents\Coralfill\Knowledge
```

Subdirectories are automatically scanned.

## Step 4: Run the Pipeline

```bash
npm run ingest:pdfs
```

