## Troubleshooting Common Issues

### Issue: No PDFs Found

**Log shows:**
```
❌ No PDFs found in C:\Users\User\Documents\Coralfill\Knowledge
```

**Solutions:**
```bash
# 1. Verify directory exists
dir "C:\Users\User\Documents\Coralfill\Knowledge"

# 2. Check for .pdf files
dir "C:\Users\User\Documents\Coralfill\Knowledge" /S *.pdf

# 3. Create directory if missing
mkdir "C:\Users\User\Documents\Coralfill\Knowledge"

# 4. Copy PDFs there and retry
npm run ingest:pdfs
```

### Issue: Supabase Connection Failed

**Log shows:**
```
❌ Failed to connect to Supabase
Error: Invalid credentials
```

**Solutions:**
```bash
# 1. Verify .env file
cat .env

# 2. Check credentials format
# Should be:
# SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=sb_secret_xxxxx

# 3. Test connection manually
node -e "console.log(process.env.SUPABASE_URL)"

# 4. Verify in Supabase dashboard
# https://app.supabase.com → Settings → API
```

### Issue: PDF Extraction Failed

**Log shows:**
```
⚠️  No readable text extracted (possibly image-based PDF)
```

**This is normal for:**
- Scanned documents without OCR
- Image-only PDFs
- Password-protected PDFs

**Solutions:**
```bash
# 1. Use online OCR (free)
# https://www.ocr.space/

# 2. Or skip and process other PDFs
# Pipeline continues with next file

# 3. Or install OCR support (advanced)
npm install tesseract.js
```

